      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/a82dd7236f495fe6698b6deb05b0ab6d9d4c0a93.png?auto=compress,format&amp;h=340&amp;w=1200&amp;s=164f4ed2d1ad480121386c2ea23a9489"&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/2bf446cf6f89c32e99d0d088edac362b814b3351.png?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=crop&amp;h=600&amp;w=1200&amp;s=d95ec61f7fcc9ae81267ed72e083b76d"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Harness the freedom to create with Godot &lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Your creative possibilities are limitless with the right game engine. Say hello to our latest Software Bundle: Learn Godot in 2025—a complete course collection designed to help you master Godot’s powerful, open-source, and beginner-friendly tools. Build any game you can imagine with step-by-step lessons like &lt;em&gt;Make a Complete Bullet Hell from Scratch in Godot &lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Make a Fully-Fledged Farming RPG with Godot&lt;/em&gt;—then, learn to upload them online with &lt;em&gt;Publishing to Steam for Godot Game Projects&lt;/em&gt;! Pay what you want for these great tools and help support NPower with your purchase.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#0"&gt;Pay $1 to unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtogodot4gamedevelopment2025edition"&gt;Intro to Godot 4 Game Development (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtothegamedevelopmentindustry"&gt;Intro to the Game Development Industry&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#publishingtosteamforgodotgameprojects"&gt;Publishing to Steam for Godot Game Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#makeacompletebullethellfromscratchingodot2025edition"&gt;Make a Complete Bullet Hell from Scratch in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#makeafully-fledgedfarmingrpgwithgodot2025edition"&gt;Make a Fully-Fledged Farming RPG with Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#2dcozysandboxingodot_unit1_playerandworld"&gt;Cozy Sandbox in Godot - Unit 1 - Player &amp; World&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#2dcozysandboxingodot_unit2_toolmechanics"&gt;Cozy Sandbox in Godot - Unit 2 - Tool Mechanics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#2dcozysandboxingodot_unit3_basebuilding"&gt;Cozy Sandbox in Godot - Unit 3 - Base Building&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit1_characters"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 1 - Characters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit2_inventory"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 2 - Inventory&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit3_world"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 3 - World&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#buildacompleteroguelikefromscratchwithgodot2025edition"&gt;Build a Complete Roguelike from Scratch with Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#makeanrtsgameingodotfromstarttofinish2025edition"&gt;Make an RTS Game in Godot from Start to Finish (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit2_cityspawning"&gt;4X Strategy Game in Godot &amp; C# - Unit 2 - City Spawning&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit3_units"&gt;4X Strategy Game in Godot &amp; C# - Unit 3 - Units&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#buildpracticalreal-worldappsusinggodot"&gt;Build Practical Real-World Apps using Godot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#buildawalkingsimulatorwithgodot4"&gt;Build a Walking Simulator with Godot 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#createacomplete2dplatformeringodot2025edition"&gt;Create a Complete 2D Platformer in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#developacomplete3dplatformeringodot2025edition"&gt;Develop a Complete 3D Platformer in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#godot4mini-projects2025edition"&gt;Godot 4 Mini-Projects (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#explorevfxwithparticlesingodot2025edition"&gt;Explore VFX with Particles in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#intermediategodot_essentialprogrammingpatterns"&gt;Intermediate Godot - Essential Programming Patterns&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#constructamultiplayerlobbyingodot"&gt;Construct a Multiplayer Lobby in Godot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#learn3dmodelingwithblenderfromscratch"&gt;Learn 3D Modeling with Blender from Scratch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#uvmappinginblenderforbeginners"&gt;UV Mapping in Blender for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtoriggingmodelsinblender"&gt;Intro to Rigging Models in Blender&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#magicavoxelforbeginners_createvoxelgameassets"&gt;MagicaVoxel for Beginners - Create Voxel Game Assets&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bta1"&gt;Pay more than the average of $29.40 to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#learnuisystemsandlayoutsforgodot"&gt;Learn UI Systems and Layouts for Godot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit1_hex-basedmap"&gt;4X Strategy Game in Godot &amp; C# - Unit 1 - Hex-Based Map&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#uiuxforgamedesign"&gt;UI/UX for Game Design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="0"&gt;Pay $1 to unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtogodot4gamedevelopment2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="introtogodot4gamedevelopment2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/dBnPIYk_pAA"&gt;Intro to Godot 4 Game Development (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Start your game development journey with Godot — the powerful, open-source game engine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From its beginner-friendly workflow to its robust capabilities for professionals, mastering Godot opens up endless possibilities in the world of game development. In this course, you'll explore the essential features of Godot by gaining hands-on experience in core development tools, 2D design, 3D environments, and coding gameplay behaviors with GDScript from start to finish.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dive in and gain the foundations you'll need to make RPGs, survival games, and more with Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate the Godot editor&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize core editing tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand Nodes and Scenes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with 2D &amp;amp; 3D assets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Script gameplay behaviors with GDScript&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a basic interactive game&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtothegamedevelopmentindustry"&gt;&lt;a id="introtothegamedevelopmentindustry" href="https://youtu.be/Bx45Zdv0woc"&gt;Intro to the Game Development Industry&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how the video game industry works!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Video games are a well-established, profitable industry with unique characteristics that support the development process. You'll explore the industry's structure by learning the overall stages of development, how work is divided by role, and more. This information will help you interact with the game industry with solid footing and have a greater understanding of how games are made.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;No prior experience with the game industry is needed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn all about:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Job roles &amp;amp; responsibilities&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Large vs. small companies&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;The development cycle&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IP copyrights&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;NDAs&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="publishingtosteamforgodotgameprojects"&gt;&lt;a id="publishingtosteamforgodotgameprojects" href="https://youtu.be/M_DZL7slM-M"&gt;Publishing to Steam for Godot Game Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Publish your Godot game to Steam with confidence!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Steamworks provides crucial tools for developers, enabling seamless publishing, player interaction, and monetization for games on Steam. In this course, you'll learn how to integrate Steamworks into your Godot project, equipping you to bring your games to a global audience as a fully-fledged Steam release. By completing the course, you’ll understand how to polish your game for publication and uncover the tools necessary to implement real-world features like achievements and player stats.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Initialize Steamworks in a Godot project&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Fetch user-specific data&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Integrate player avatars into the UI&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Track and unlock Steam achievements&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Modify and display in-game stats&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Prepare your game for Steam publishing&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="makeacompletebullethellfromscratchingodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="makeacompletebullethellfromscratchingodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/XK94Rmlj-dU"&gt;Make a Complete Bullet Hell from Scratch in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Craft a fully-fledged bullet hell game in Godot!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Bullet hell games are renowned for their fast-paced action, dense attack patterns, and the technical challenge of managing hundreds of objects on screen - making them a fantastic way to advance your game development skills. In this course, you’ll build a complete bullet hell experience, mastering techniques such as node pooling, scene inheritance, and randomization. These new skills will vastly enhance your Godot skills and enable you to make increasingly complex games with many objects.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Implement efficient object pooling&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Utilize scene inheritance for scaling&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create dynamic object spawn systems&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Work with sprite sheets and tilemaps&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Add polished audio and SFX&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Design pickups and stat upgrades&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="makeafully-fledgedfarmingrpgwithgodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="makeafully-fledgedfarmingrpgwithgodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/IJPEw0SvLHE"&gt;Make a Fully-Fledged Farming RPG with Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create a farming RPG from start to finish in Godot!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Farming RPGs are a cornerstone of the game development world, seamlessly blending creativity, resource management, and engaging progression systems. In this course, you’ll build a complete tile-based farming RPG complete with seed planting, crop nurturing, harvesting, and more. By mastering the modular concepts featured, you'll be ready to expand these skills for your own project or add farming mechanics to any existing Godot project.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Interact with and modify TileMaps&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Use Autoloads for global managers&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Script crop growth and harvesting cycles&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Handle in-game purchases and inventory&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Organize logic with GDScript dictionaries&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Structure mechanics with custom GDScript classes&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="2dcozysandboxingodot_unit1_playerandworld"&gt;&lt;a id="2dcozysandboxingodot_unit1_playerandworld" href="https://youtu.be/6bSSIdnGDHY"&gt;Cozy Sandbox in Godot - Unit 1 - Player &amp; World&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build the core systems behind your own 2D cozy sandbox game!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A charming sandbox experience begins with a lively player and a richly interactive world - essentials that bring cozy games to life and make the genre popular with players. In this course, you’ll create a complete player character with detailed animations, design tile-based worlds with auto-tiling, and add atmosphere using day-night cycles and background music. With these skills, you’ll be ready to implement 2D animations or tilemaps in any future Godot project with streamlined techniques!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Set up animated player characters&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Master AnimationTree for movement&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create layered TileMap environments&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Implement auto-tiling techniques&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Build seamless day/night cycles&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Add background music and SFX&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="2dcozysandboxingodot_unit2_toolmechanics"&gt;&lt;a id="2dcozysandboxingodot_unit2_toolmechanics" href="https://youtu.be/EnoMhuAKXYQ"&gt;Cozy Sandbox in Godot - Unit 2 - Tool Mechanics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unlock interactive tool mechanics for your cozy sandbox adventure!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tool mechanics breathe life into sandbox games, enabling players to build, farm, and explore with creativity. In this course, you’ll develop a complete tool system for your 2D Godot game while mastering system toggling and unique interactions for tools like watering cans, axes, and more. These skills will give you the modular techniques needed to add tools to any game and connect different, complex game systems together with ease!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;An intermediate understanding of Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize enums and data typing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manipulate TileMap layers via script&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up basic combat systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build plant growing systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create interactive tool mechanics end-to-end&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add basic weather to games&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="2dcozysandboxingodot_unit3_basebuilding"&gt;&lt;a id="2dcozysandboxingodot_unit3_basebuilding" href="https://youtu.be/Qs6PKaL9Fp4"&gt;Cozy Sandbox in Godot - Unit 3 - Base Building&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a fully-fledged base-building system in your own cozy sandbox game!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Base building and resource management are essential skills for sandbox games that invite creativity and replayability. In this course, you'll expand a 2D tile-based world with a construction mechanic, letting players gather resources and shape their environment. By weaving together multiple complex features, you’ll master integrating systems vital for advanced sandbox game development and set the stage for larger-scale, real-world Godot projects.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Implement player-driven building systems&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Design resource gathering mechanics&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Work with advanced TileMap layers&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Dynamically place objects in game worlds&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Integrate tools, resources, and UI&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Organize code for complex features&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit1_characters"&gt;&lt;a id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit1_characters" href="https://youtu.be/eViQ0nDdX3E"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 1 - Characters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build an epic 3D action-adventure game from start to finish!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Action-adventure games, with their immersive gameplay and dynamic challenges, are a staple of modern gaming. Through this course, you'll explore the basics of creating characters in Godot - developing smooth animations, dynamic combat mechanics, and randomized enemies to bring your game to life. By mastering these techniques, you’ll be ready to expand into creating other 3D genres with confidence and add more advanced features to your action-adventure project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design and configure a 3D character&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Animate actions with Godot’s animation trees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add multiple weapons and shields&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate enemies with random appearances&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Program player combat mechanics, including defending&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with inheritance for cleaner code&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit2_inventory"&gt;&lt;a id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit2_inventory" href="https://youtu.be/IcuOueQiHbQ"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 2 - Inventory&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master advanced inventory systems for 3D action-adventure games in Godot!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Inventory systems are a cornerstone of action-adventure games, enhancing player engagement by providing seamless item management and customization options. Through this course, you'll construct a complete inventory system from start to finish, enabling players to select weapons, shields, and style items with a dynamic 3D preview. These skills will empower you to develop robust inventory management for immersive game worlds.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Build dynamic UI layouts with Godot&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create inventory systems for equippable items&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Implement 3D item preview functionality&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Work with anchors, containers, and layout nodes&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Develop interactivity using GDScript logic&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Add visual enhancements to improve aesthetics&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit3_world"&gt;&lt;a id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit3_world" href="https://youtu.be/UWRmLIqbRy8"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 3 - World&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create fully-fledged 3D levels in Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Action-adventure games hinge on immersive environments, and creating compelling levels is a crucial skill for any game developer. In this course, you'll create two distinct 3D levels - an overworld imported from Blender and a modular castle built with Godot's grid maps - while enhancing them with custom shaders for water, grass, and lava to blend functionality with visual appeal. By the end, you’ll have the skills to complete your own fully-fledged action-adventure game, ready to expand into more complex 3D projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use 3D models from Blender&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create modular levels with grid maps&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build shaders for water, grass, &amp;amp; lava&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement level transition systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add environmental variety for player immersion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement item pickups&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildacompleteroguelikefromscratchwithgodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="buildacompleteroguelikefromscratchwithgodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/h5bdE7nFGuc"&gt;Build a Complete Roguelike from Scratch with Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master roguelike development from start to finish with Godot.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A staple of game development, the roguelike genre provides a framework for creating endlessly replayable and dynamic experiences for players. Through this course, you’ll construct a fully-fledged, action-packed roguelike game featuring procedural generation, challenging enemies, and powerful items. These modular-based skills will empower you to customize and expand upon the project, creating unique and complex roguelike worlds of your own.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Generate procedural room layouts&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Design unique enemies and bosses&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Implement a functional mini-map&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Add sounds and damage visuals&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create collectible player items&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Manage room states with doors&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="makeanrtsgameingodotfromstarttofinish2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="makeanrtsgameingodotfromstarttofinish2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/iO6QcnVPVrU"&gt;Make an RTS Game in Godot from Start to Finish (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a real-time strategy game from start to finish in Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;RTS games challenge players to think on their feet and make strategic decisions in dynamic environments. In this course, you'll create an engaging RTS game featuring player-controlled units, an AI team, and strategy-driven gameplay using modular systems. By creating an RTS game, you’ll explore one of gaming's most exciting genres while mastering key development skills like AI behavior, navigation systems, and game mechanics—unlocking opportunities for more advanced projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design real-time strategy gameplay mechanics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement player-controlled unit selection&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Program AI units with pathfinding&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply navigation systems to avoid obstacles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create dynamic win/loss systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add game juice and polish&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit2_cityspawning"&gt;&lt;a id="4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit2_cityspawning" href="https://youtu.be/fD3KIa6-TNI"&gt;4X Strategy Game in Godot &amp; C# - Unit 2 - City Spawning&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Explore spawning resources, cities, and more for 4X strategy games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cities are an integral part of 4X strategy game development and represent one of the core mechanics of how they work. In this course, you'll master the intricacies of city spawning on a procedural hexagonal-based map and advanced UI management using Godot and C#. These skills will enable you to further master strategy game development and expand procedural map generation with functional game mechanics.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A solid understanding of Godot and C# is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Select and manipulate hex map tiles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add randomized resources to tiles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage UI events effectively&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Differentiate signals and delegates&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spawn and manage game cities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate random faction colors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit3_units"&gt;&lt;a id="4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit3_units" href="https://youtu.be/8sigPJC-Gd0"&gt;4X Strategy Game in Godot &amp; C# - Unit 3 - Units&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Expand your knowledge of 4X strategy games by learning how to spawn and manage units!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unit mechanics are crucial for creating immersive 4X experiences - and a deep understanding of these will drive the exploration of your games. In this course, you'll use Godot and C# to build a comprehensive unit system, as well as implement a customizable main menu. These skills will not only round out your 4X strategy game-making skills, but open the doors to even more advanced strategy mechanics.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A solid understanding of Godot and C# is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spawn units from cities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Display unit data with UIs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Move units on the map&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement unit combat mechanics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Capture cities using units&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create customizable overlays and menus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildpracticalreal-worldappsusinggodot"&gt;&lt;a id="buildpracticalreal-worldappsusinggodot" href="https://youtu.be/Yod56xV1LVY"&gt;Build Practical Real-World Apps using Godot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master real-world app development with Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Godot isn’t just for games - this versatile, open-source engine is perfect for creating useful, fully-fledged applications as well! In this course, you’ll build two complete projects from start to finish: a calculator and a Body Mass Index (BMI) measurer, each with fully functional light and dark modes. By the end, you'll have a great understanding of how to harness Godot’s powerful tools and elevate your skills to tackle even more complex real-world projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design themes with Godot’s styling tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Validate and filter user input effectively&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Write dynamic calculations using expressions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Toggle between light and dark UI modes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Optimize apps with advanced node structures&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Explore Godot’s potential beyond game creation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildawalkingsimulatorwithgodot4"&gt;&lt;a id="buildawalkingsimulatorwithgodot4" href="https://youtu.be/STGr8QRB7Ao"&gt;Build a Walking Simulator with Godot 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover the fundamentals for walking simulators in Godot 4!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Walking simulators are a popular genre for storytellers looking for new ways to convey atmosphere and visuals with their tales. In this course, you'll create modular systems for players and interactive elements that can easily be dragged and dropped into any sort of walking simulator-like game. These skills will provide you with the core features to be able to tell a multitude of stories and expand into similar genres such as horror, survival, and more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Basic familiarity with Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up input controls&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate navigatable terrain&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with first-person cameras&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement walking, sprinting, and jumping&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Improve overall game feel&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create multi-use interaction systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="createacomplete2dplatformeringodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="createacomplete2dplatformeringodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/q_FVagfyQ5g"&gt;Create a Complete 2D Platformer in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a fully-fledged 2D platformer using Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Creating platformer games is one of the most exciting and versatile ways to explore 2D game mechanics, with a great blend of player movement, enemy AI, and interactive objects. In this course, you'll construct a complete 2D platformer game from scratch – learning core mechanics like platforming fundamentals, health systems, coin collection, and level progression. By the end, you’ll have a polished, engaging 2D platformer and the skills to expand into any sort of 2D game you might imagine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up a fully functional player&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create enemies with basic AI behavior&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design and implement a health system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add a coin collection and scoring system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use persistent data across multiple scenes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up level transitions with end flags&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="developacomplete3dplatformeringodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="developacomplete3dplatformeringodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/DwOXkHwH4eM"&gt;Develop a Complete 3D Platformer in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Craft a complete 3D platformer game from start to finish!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;3D platformers are a staple of game design, combining engaging challenges with rewarding exploration across dynamic environments. In this course, you’ll harness the power of Godot to create a fully-fledged 3D platformer game, complete with collectible items, enemy hazards, and multiple levels. By walking through every step of development, you’ll not only build a compelling game but also gain practical experience that will equip you to tackle even more complex 3D game projects.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Set up levels using Godot's 3D tools&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create a responsive player controller&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Enhance player movements with visual feedback&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Implement collectibles with scores and effects&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Design custom enemy behaviors&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Build seamless level transitions&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="godot4mini-projects2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="godot4mini-projects2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/dJDsLgDli18"&gt;Godot 4 Mini-Projects (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn essential game development tools through engaging Godot mini-projects!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Godot is a leading open-source game engine known for its flexibility in creating both 2D and 3D games. In this course, you'll create four practical mini-projects designed to solidify your grasp on crucial game mechanics and programming concepts. From mouse input handling to 2D physics systems and collision detection, these hands-on projects will form the foundation needed to build more complex, complete games in the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement mouse-click-driven interactions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Godot’s physics engine&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect collisions and handle responses&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use loops to automate complex systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create dynamic UI for player interaction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Communicate between scripts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="explorevfxwithparticlesingodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="explorevfxwithparticlesingodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/tdGYcVccAVA"&gt;Explore VFX with Particles in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bring your games to life with dazzling visual effects in Godot!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;No matter the game, particles can provide the magic touch that transforms ordinary scenes into unforgettable moments. Through this course, you’ll dive into Godot's flexible particle system as you build a suite of five real-world effects, including fire, rain, and more. These projects will help you master the core settings and tools needed to create unique visual effects - which can easily be applied to your own Godot projects!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Work with versatile particle emitters&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create sparks with gravity and collision&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Design immersive fire and smoke effects&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Script interactive walking dirt trails&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Craft custom impact (hit) particles&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Simulate atmospheric rain with collisions&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="intermediategodot_essentialprogrammingpatterns"&gt;&lt;a id="intermediategodot_essentialprogrammingpatterns" href="https://youtu.be/KnO-Q9nvPQY"&gt;Intermediate Godot - Essential Programming Patterns&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unlock the power of coding design patterns in Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mastering design patterns is crucial for creating scalable and modular game code - regardless of the project you're building. Through this course, you'll deepen your understanding of GDScript by implementing the SOLID principles alongside industry-standard coding patterns. These insights into programming patterns will empower you to tackle more ambitious game projects, ensuring your skills evolve from start to finish.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;An intermediate understanding of Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply SOLID coding principles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement singletons in Godot&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use the observer pattern effectively&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute the command pattern&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master object pooling techniques&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Optimize for scalable game design&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="constructamultiplayerlobbyingodot"&gt;&lt;a id="constructamultiplayerlobbyingodot" href="https://youtu.be/F5H2oRo91lU"&gt;Construct a Multiplayer Lobby in Godot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a multiplayer lobby with Godot's networking tools!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multiplayer is a core feature in many of today’s most popular games, offering engaging social experiences for players. In this course, you'll create a complete multiplayer lobby system with player joining, management tools, and seamless game scene transitions, ready to integrate into a sample multiplayer platformer game. By mastering these concepts, you’ll have the confidence to implement robust player management systems for any kind of multiplayer game you have in mind.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Connect players using IP and port setup&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Construct UI elements for lobby systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Display users by username&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Individualize host and client control tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Transition players into game scenes seamlessly&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Synchronize player input using server logic&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="learn3dmodelingwithblenderfromscratch"&gt;&lt;a id="learn3dmodelingwithblenderfromscratch" href="https://youtu.be/AC557GnNGqQ"&gt;Learn 3D Modeling with Blender from Scratch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master the foundations of Blender and 3D modeling!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3D modeling, the process of creating digital 3D objects, is a robust field of study with real-world applications for animation, game development, and more. In this course, you'll explore the free and open-source Blender software and learn the fundamental techniques for manipulating meshes and creating custom assets. These skills will form the basis for expanding your 3D modeling skills and open up opportunities to create unique assets for your projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No prior experience is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand how 3D objects work&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Move, rotate, and scale objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Edit vertices, edges, and faces&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Blender's modifiers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply materials to meshes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Export models for other programs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="uvmappinginblenderforbeginners"&gt;&lt;a id="uvmappinginblenderforbeginners" href="https://youtu.be/bCMPqxpxZis"&gt;UV Mapping in Blender for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master texturing in Blender by learning how to use UV maps!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;UV mapping - a process by which you "unwrap" a 3D model into a flat surface - offers creators an easy way to paint complex textures. You'll explore creating UV maps for different 3D objects and set them up to suit your material's needs. These skills in UV mapping will provide you with key techniques to customize your 3D graphics to your exact specifications.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This course assumes basic familiarity with Blender.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Apply textures to an object&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create UV maps for primitive shapes&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Build models suitable for UV mapping&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Combine techniques to unwrap complex objects&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Export UV maps for 2D software&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Paint textures onto a flattened UV map&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtoriggingmodelsinblender"&gt;&lt;a id="introtoriggingmodelsinblender" href="https://youtu.be/tVccjBYF2Ic"&gt;Intro to Rigging Models in Blender&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Prepare your 3D models for animation!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rigging is an important technique for 3D animation by which one creates a skeletal-like armature that can be manipulated to move parts of the 3D mesh around. You’ll discover everything required for rigging – from setting up the “bones” to weight painting and controlling which parts of the mesh are affected by each bone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;By the end, you’ll have the foundations you’ll need to master rigging any kind of 3D model and expand your skills in creating custom assets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create bones to build an armature&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Connect your armature and 3D mesh&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Control affected vertices with weight painting&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Export rigged models&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Apply Mixamo animations to your models&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="magicavoxelforbeginners_createvoxelgameassets"&gt;&lt;a id="magicavoxelforbeginners_createvoxelgameassets" href="https://youtu.be/jJDHSG20ZJQ"&gt;MagicaVoxel for Beginners - Create Voxel Game Assets&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Not an artist, but eager to create Minecraft-style voxel art models for your Unity games? Discover how to build your own 3D game models with MagicaVoxel - the free program that will enable you to build simple game models and environment. No experience in MagicaVoxel, 3D modeling or artistic experience is required - you will be shown how to use the essential tools from scratch, and how to export them into Unity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Topics included&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Using the different brushes and tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Camera controls to navigate your scene&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Creating a voxel art tree, a character, and a landscape&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Importing models into Unity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working with color palettes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bta1"&gt;Pay more than the average of $29.40 to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="learnuisystemsandlayoutsforgodot"&gt;&lt;a id="learnuisystemsandlayoutsforgodot" href="https://youtu.be/4lBGYatr95A"&gt;Learn UI Systems and Layouts for Godot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master the essentials of designing responsive game UIs with Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;User interfaces (UI) are a core element of any game, bridging the gap between gameplay and the player’s experience. In this course, you will gain hands-on experience creating fully-fledged menus and UI layouts using Godot’s powerful layout system. By the end, you’ll have the skills to craft dynamic, adaptable interfaces ready for use in real-world game projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Place and position UI elements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add custom themes to your UI&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Handle controller input for usability&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use containers for dynamic layouts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with presets and customizations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design adaptable, scalable UI systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit1_hex-basedmap"&gt;&lt;a id="4xstrategygameingodotandc_unit1_hex-basedmap" href="https://youtu.be/d8fS0aCHe8A"&gt;4X Strategy Game in Godot &amp; C# - Unit 1 - Hex-Based Map&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unlock the secrets to creating engaging 4X strategy games from scratch!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Strategy games are known for their rich mechanics and complex features, with many rooted in hex-based map designs. In this course, you’ll embark on a journey to develop a turn-based strategy game using Godot and C# by learning the essential skills for creating a map from hexagonal tiles. These skills will not only put you on the starting path for making strategy games, but give you map skills that can be used in a variety of other genres and projects!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create procedural terrain generation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Godot's tilemap layers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement camera panning &amp;amp; zooming&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Handle mouse input for map scrolling&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize the FastNoiseLite generator&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply C# LINQ for data queries&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="uiuxforgamedesign"&gt;&lt;a id="uiuxforgamedesign" href="https://youtu.be/f0tBF6qfoMc"&gt;UI/UX for Game Design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover UI and UX design principles for games!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The user interface and user experience play a critical role in communicating information to players and creating smooth, interactive gameplay. In this course, you'll build a UI/UX mockup for a mobile game while exploring design methodologies and wireframing techniques. These techniques will provide you new ways to approach UI/UX game design and to meaningfully apply iterative design to optimize your game's experience.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Understand users with user stories&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Create definitive design criteria&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Utilize wireframes for mockups&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Apply common design conventions&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Test and iterate design choices&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Recognize design processes&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
